SIMPLE: saving
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saving
<hw>Sav"ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Preserving; rescuing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He is the <qex>saving</qex> strength of his anointed.</q>
<rj><qau>Ps. xxviii. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Avoiding unnecessary expense or waste; frugal; not
lavish or wasteful; economical; <as>as, a <ex>saving</ex>
cook</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Bringing back in returns or in receipts the sum
expended; incurring no loss, though not gainful; <as>as, a
<ex>saving</ex> bargain; the ship has made a <ex>saving</ex>
voyage</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Making reservation or exception; <as>as, a
<ex>saving</ex> clause</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Saving</xex> is often used with a noun to form a
compound adjective; <as>as, labor-<ex>saving</ex>, life-<ex>saving</ex>,
etc.</as></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1280 pr=PCP --></p>

<p><ent>Saving</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Saving
<hw>Sav"ing</hw> <pr>(s⟦amac⟧v"⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <pos>prep. ⟦or⟧
conj.</pos>; but properly a <pos>participle</pos>. <def>With the
exception of; except; excepting; also, without disrespect to.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Saving</xex> your reverence.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Saving</xex> your presence.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Burns.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>None of us put off our clothes, <qex>saving</qex> that every one
put them off for washing.</q> <rj><qau>Neh. iv. 23.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And in the stone a new name written, which no man knoweth
<qex>saving</qex> he that receiveth it.</q> <rj><qau>Rev. ii.
17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saving</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Saving
<hw>Sav"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Something kept from
being expended or lost; that which is saved or laid up; <as>as, the
<ex>savings</ex> of years of economy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Exception; reservation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Contend not with those that are too strong for us, but still with
a <qex>saving</qex> to honesty.</q> <rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Savings bank</b></col>, <cd>a bank in which savings or
earnings are deposited and put at interest.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Savingly</ent>⟦br⟧
